hen under pressure.", "thoughts": "We need to answer based on given info. Summarize each:\n\nCandidate A reliability or calmness under pressure: No explicit info. We have ability to anticipate dangerous situations, see complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities, unfriendly, eats unhealthily. No reliability or calmness.\n\nCandidate D teamwork/communication strengths and willingness to develop professionally: No explicit info on teamwork/communication strengths. We have \"responds to unexpected events adequately\", \"can concentrate very well\", \"solves problems extremely well\", \"takes responsibility seriously\", \"considered moody\", \"loner\", \"regarded as a know-it-all\". No mention of willingness to develop professionally. So answer: no info.\n\nCandidate C calmness under pressure: We have \"handles stress very well\" (I think from earlier? Actually in the list we have: \"Candidate C handles stress very well.\" Yes, that was in the initial list? Let's check original candidate info: The list includes: \"Candidate C handles stress very well.\" Yes, it's there. Also \"Candidate C can make correct decisions quickly.\" So we have calmness under pressure: handles stress very well. So we have info: yes, candidate C handles stress well, indicating calmness under pressure.\n\nThus answer: A: no info; D: no info on teamwork strengths or professional development; C: handles stress very well, indicating calm under pressure.\n\nWe must mention uncertainty where appropriate. Provide concise answer."}
